╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
Process intercepted transmissions to extract repair instructions sent
from Earth. The data is corrupted and fragmented - you'll need to use
data pipelines to filter and extract the useful information.

This sector contains three sub-missions:
    1. transmissions/  - Process raw signal data using pipes
    2. signals/        - Parse structured transmission logs
    3. decrypted/      - Final decoding challenge

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

COMMAND REFERENCE:

    PIPES - Chain commands together:
    command1 | command2 | command3

    VIEW FILES:
    head -n 10 file       First 10 lines
    tail -n 10 file       Last 10 lines
    tail -n +5 file       Everything from line 5 onwards

    SORT & FILTER:
    sort file             Sort lines alphabetically
    sort -n file          Sort numerically
    sort -r file          Reverse sort
    uniq                  Remove adjacent duplicates
    sort | uniq           Sort then deduplicate

    EXTRACT FIELDS:
    cut -d',' -f2 file    Get 2nd comma-separated field
    cut -d':' -f1 file    Get 1st colon-separated field
    awk '{print $3}'      Get 3rd whitespace-separated field

    REDIRECT OUTPUT:
    command > file        Write output to file (overwrite)
    command >> file       Append output to file

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

